FRONTLINE ROADS v0.31.3 COMMAND CAPACITY / FACILITY GUIDANCE / RESOURCE HUD AUDIT

Release: 0.31.3-command-capacity-resource-hud
Save key: unchanged (frontline_roads_refactor_v2)
Schema version: unchanged (2)

PHASE 1 — BASE SQUAD CAPACITY
- Removed the fixed one-squad-per-base constant.
- Major-base capacity is derived as 2 + civilization level.
- Field-base capacity is derived as 2 + floor(civilization level / 2).
- Active, recovering and ready squads each occupy one persistent slot.
- A recovering squad no longer blocks unrelated free slots.
- Same-type ready squads retain free redeployment.
- Different-type ready squads are replaced only when all slots are occupied.
- Coordinated deployment reserves squad slots, not whole bases, so one base may launch several formation members.
- Capacity is derived at runtime; no save migration or duplicated stored capacity value was added.

PHASE 2 — SETTLEMENT FACILITY GUIDANCE
- Every settlement building has a concise description.
- Catalog cards show purpose before construction.
- Production cards keep the same explanation after construction.
- Descriptions state production/storage effect and the principal downstream use.

PHASE 3 — RESOURCE HUD
- Removed the hand-picked seven-resource summary list.
- HUD now iterates canonical RESOURCE_KEYS.
- Wood, stone and fiber are always present.
- Every owned or overflowed advanced resource appears as an independent chip.
- The dock uses two fixed-height rows with horizontal scrolling.
- Portrait controls, resource dock, base summary and warning use separate vertical bands.
- Low-height landscape uses a one-row resource dock beneath the action row.

GAMEPLAY / COMPATIBILITY CHECKS
- Major-base capacity progression: 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 for Civilization Lv.0–4.
- Field-base capacity progression: 2, 2, 3, 3, 4 for Civilization Lv.0–4.
- Multiple assault squads can leave one base until capacity is full.
- Recovery occupies one slot while other slots remain deployable.
- Field bases can launch multiple approved light squads.
- Coordinated formations may use several slots from the nearest suitable base.
- Conservative opening strategy still reaches Civilization Lv.1 on line, cross and grid networks without city defeat or squad loss.
- Attack-only opening still incurs meaningful material losses.
- Existing save/restore, recovery, retrieval, tactical-order and long-run tests remain valid.

